<in-bse-fin:DisclosureOfNotesOnFinancialResultsExplanatoryTextBlock contextRef="OneD">Notes:  n1. The above results have been approved and taken on record by the Board of Directors at its meeting held on 23rd October, 2018.  n2. The Competition Commission of India (CCI), vide its order dated 31st August, 2016 had imposed a penalty of Rs 1,163.91 crore on the Company. On Company’s appeal, the Competition Appellate Tribunal (COMPAT), subsequently merged with National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT), vide its interim Order had granted stay against the CCI’s Order with a condition to deposit 10% of the penalty amount.  nNCLAT, vide its Order dated 25th July, 2018, dismissed the Company's appeal and upheld the CCI’s order. Against this, the Company appealed to the Hon'ble Supreme Court, which by its order dated 5th October, 2018 admitted the appeal and directed to continue the interim order passed by the Tribunal, in the meantime.  nIn a separate matter, pursuant to a reference filed by the Director, Supplies and Disposals, Government of Haryana, the CCI by its Order dated 19th January, 2017 had imposed a penalty of Rs 29.84 crore on the Company. On Company's appeal, COMPAT, has stayed the operation of CCI’s order in the meanwhile. The matter is pending for hearing before NCLAT.   nBased on the advice of external legal counsel, the Company believes it has good grounds on merit for a successful appeal in both the aforesaid matters. Accordingly, no provision is made in the above financial results.  n3. The Government of India introduced the Goods and Services Tax (GST) with effect from 1st July, 2017. Excise duty forms part of revenue for the nine months ended 30th September, 2017 and year ended 31st December, 2017.  n4. The Company is exclusively engaged in the business of cement and cement related products.  n5. The figures for the previous period have been regrouped / reclassified wherever necessary to conform to the current period's presentation.  n6. Limited review of the financial results for the quarter and nine months ended 30th September, 2018 has been carried out by the statutory auditors. </in-bse-fin:DisclosureOfNotesOnFinancialResultsExplanatoryTextBlock>
